        <description>&lt;i&gt;Parodius: The Octopus Saves the Earth&lt;/i&gt; is the first game in the &lt;i&gt;Parodius&lt;/i&gt; series, although this position is often confused with the better-known second game. &amp;quot;Parodius&amp;quot; is a portmanteau of &amp;quot;Gradius&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Parody,&amp;quot; and &lt;i&gt;Parodius&lt;/i&gt; is a parody of &lt;a href="/game/gradius"&gt;Gradius&lt;/a&gt;. Gameplay is similar to &lt;i&gt;Gradius&lt;/i&gt;, a horizontal scrolling shooter, but you play as silly characters from Konami games and Japanese pop culture, such as Takosuke the octopus and the Penguin from &lt;a href="/game/antarctic-adventure"&gt;Antarctic Adventure&lt;/a&gt;. There are six stages with various obstacles and enemies, and it uses a similar selection-bar based power-up system to &lt;i&gt;Gradius&lt;/i&gt;.</description>
